        <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2011-07-28T21:57:04.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>You pass a Zend_Json_Server instance to Zend_Json_Server_Cache::saveSmd($file, $server). Typically, you'd then grab the SMD from the cache using Zend_Json_Server_Cache::getSmd($file) on subsequent requests, returning it directly to the client. You can therefore check the file generated to see if it contains return information.</p>

        </div>
